2pt">elivered in their force area. They</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> must ensure that the chief officer has appropriate processes in place for dealing with complaints, conduct matters and death and serious injury</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (DSI)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> matters.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Where it appears to a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">PCC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that the chief officer has not complied with this obligation, or has contravened it, the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">PCC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> can direct the chief officer to take appropriate steps to address this. The chief officer must comply with any directions given in such circumstances.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">PCC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is also the appropriate authority for any complaints, conduct</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> matters</span><span style="font-family:Arial; fo