n><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n the po</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">lice complaints system</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">However, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">esponsibility </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for public confidence does not simply lie with the IPCC. It rests with all the bodies </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and individuals involved – Police and Crime Commissioners, Chief Constables, the College of Policing, H</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">er </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">M</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ajesty's</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Inspectorate of Constabulary and the Home Office. All have their distinct but vital roles to play.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The IPCC is committed to work</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> with PCCs and other agencies to achieve this aim and improve </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">both the way complaints are handled and the way policing is carried out</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. This will be achieved </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">by</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> develop</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> systems to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> improve accessibility of the system,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> shar</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> learning from complain</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ts and investigations and ensuring</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that this learning</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> forms a virtuous circle</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to shape and improve operational policing.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">PCCs have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a pivotal </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">role in this process by</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ensuring that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the complaints system is ac</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">cessible at a local level and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">operatin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">g efficiently and equitably. The IPCC is helping PCCs achieve this by sharing quarterly information on force performance in handling complaints and qualitative information on trends and patterns in complaints handling.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  As part of the development of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">its </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">oversight and confidence work, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the IPCC is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> piloting methods of providing more detailed analysis and sampling of the handling of certain types of complaints, and the issues that are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">being complained about.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The IPCC </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will be publishing the initial findings of these pilots in January, and sharing the results with PCCs.   </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In legislation currently before Parliament, chief officers will be required to make a formal response to IPCC recommendations </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">within 56 days of the report of an investigation being issued.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> The IPCC, and the forces and PCCs concerned, will publish the recommendations and responses. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The IPCC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will want to work closely with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">PCC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial;